  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 8:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἶς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", either “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "one",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", a scribe” (Weiss and very decidedly Meyer, who says that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἶς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " never in N. T. = ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὶς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), or “a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "certain",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " scribe,” indefinite reference, so Fritzsche, falling back on Suicer, I., p. 1037, and more recently Bleek and others. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Vide",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Winer, § xviii. 9, who defends the use of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἶς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὶς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as a feature of later Greek.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "γραμματεὺς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", a scribe! even one of that most unimpressionable class, in spirit and tendency utterly opposed to the ways of Jesus. A Saul among the prophets. He has actually become warmed up to something like enthusiasm. A striking tribute to the magnetic influence of Jesus.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀκολουθήσω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": already more or less of a disciple—perhaps he had been present during the teaching on the hill or at the encounter between Jesus and the scribes in re washing (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 15:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " f.), and been filled with admiration for His wisdom, moral earnestness and courage; and this is the result. Quite honestly meant, but.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
